  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>waxy&nbsp;potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 15-20 min or until fork-tender</p>\r\n<p>Once tender, drain and return to the pot to keep warm&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pork-escalopes-walnut-and-sultana-salsa/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut each <strong>pork tenderloin</strong> in half</p>\r\n<p>Wrap the<strong>&nbsp;pork tenderloin</strong>&nbsp;halves in <strong>cling film</strong> and bash them with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> until flat and doubled in size &ndash; these are your <strong>pork escalopes&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pork-escalopes-walnut-and-sultana-salsa/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a handful of <strong>flour</strong> to a plate</p>\r\n<p>Crack the <strong>egg<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into a shallow bowl and beat with a fork</p>\r\n<p>Combine the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and <strong>dried sage</strong>&nbsp;on a plate &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Coat the<strong> pork escalopes</strong> in the <strong>flour</strong>, tap off the excess, then put them into the<strong> beaten egg</strong> and finally press them into the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> firmly to coat everything evenly</p>\r\n<p>Cover and refrigerate until later&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pork-escalopes-walnut-and-sultana-salsa/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>walnuts</strong> finely</p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>sultanas</strong> finely</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pork-escalopes-walnut-and-sultana-salsa/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the<strong> chopped parsley</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>walnuts</strong>&nbsp;and <strong>sultanas&nbsp;</strong>in a medium bowl&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>apple</strong>&nbsp;<strong>cider vinegar</strong>, 3 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [6 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of both <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Give everything a good old mix up &ndash;&nbsp;this is your <strong>walnut salsa</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pork-escalopes-walnut-and-sultana-salsa/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>pork escalopes</strong> and cook on each side for 2 min or until browned and cooked through</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pork-escalopes-walnut-and-sultana-salsa/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> to the cooked<strong> potatoes</strong> and re-heat the pot over a medium heat, crushing the potatoes lightly with a masher or fork as you go</p>\r\n<p>Slice the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p>\r\n<p>Wash the&nbsp;<strong>rocket</strong>&nbsp;<strong>salad</strong>, then add it to a large bowl with the&nbsp;<strong>sliced tomatoes</strong></p>\r\n<p>Dress with a splash of the <strong>walnut salsa&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pork-escalopes-walnut-and-sultana-salsa/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pork escalopes&nbsp;</strong>with<strong>&nbsp;</strong>the <strong>rocket salad</strong> and <strong>crushed potatoes</strong> to the side</p>\r\n<p>Drizzle with the remaining<strong> walnut salsa</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
